I have to agree with you Frank on what you&#39;ve said.  You know the approach that I&#39;ve taken so far with the box is to not take anything they say as necessarily true because of course people/spirits lie, and of course people/spirits can also be innocently mistaken or misinformed.  However, if you get messages that sound like they might be important, how can you not share them?  We&#39;ve all heard them, Frank&#39;s not lying or crazy, the only thing left to determine is whether or not the voices are lying or clueless.  That&#39;s the only thing left to determine.  Frank has done his duty by sharing them. I don&#39;t understand why people take such pleasure in lashing out at you Frank.  I guess because you&#39;re coming out with a radical new idea you&#39;re an easy target for the bullies, isn&#39;t that always how the story goes, someone is courageous enough to extend their hand sharing something new and the people bite his hand off.  I think the following is fitting here:

http://llerrah.com/doitanyway.htm

And you know what?  I recently had a ghost box message that sounds like it might be appropriate for our times too, I&#39;ve been hesitant about posting it, but if Frank&#39;s brave enough to post his stuff, I can be brave enough to post mine.  They&#39;re saying &quot;there&#39;s world war&quot;  I got this on January 21, a week after Tunisia&#39;s leader was ousted... and look now, there really is revolution cropping up everywhere... dunno if world war is referring to an all out two-sided world war, or just referring to how there&#39;s revolution popping up everywhere right now... either way I&#39;m posting it now, f- it, lol!  

Sweet God, why is everyone so mean and malicious to each other on these ghost box boards, and whenever you tell someone the truth as you see it, they act like you just shot their dog or something....  seriously, to the vast majority of the rest of the world they look at us ALL OF US like a bunch of kooky mo-fo&#39;s, so I don&#39;t see why we have to argue so much and so personally about all the petty details of what we are dealing with... when is the last time someone on these boards felt that they could freely express their joys, fears, and true opinions about their work and about each other, without feeling like they might be knocked down with a sledgehammer?  Seriously, when&#39;s the last time there has been a fun, relaxed atmosphere?    Y&#39;all need to get over yourselves, life&#39;s too short, LOVE each other, stop cr***ing on each other for speaking your mind.... now that I&#39;ve been here long enough on these here boards, to see a few things myself, that&#39;s STILL my opinion, like it was from day one.....


